\section{Cohomology of an open in \texorpdfstring{$\ModuleCat\,k$}{ModuleCat k} flavor (iter-013)}
\label{sec:hmodule_prime}

The iter-013 work scaffolds a new declaration $\HModulePrime$ in \texttt{Cohomology/StructureSheafModuleK.lean}, parallel to Mathlib's \lstinline{Sheaf.H' F n X} (file \texttt{Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/SheafCohomology/Basic.lean}, L105) for $\AddCommGrpCat$-valued sheaves. The new declaration is the \emph{cohomology of an open} in $\ModuleCat\,k$ flavor, the API entry point that downstream Mayer-Vietoris LES (queued iter-014+) and Čech-vs-derived-functor comparison theorems (queued iter-015+) both consume.

\begin{definition}[Cohomology of an open with \texorpdfstring{$\ModuleCat\,k$}{ModuleCat k} coefficients (iter-013)]
  \label{def:Scheme_HModule_prime}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.HModule'}
  \uses{def:Scheme_HModule}
  Let $k$ be a field, $(C, J)$ a Grothendieck site with $C : \mathrm{Type}\,v$ and $\Category.\{u, v\}\,C$, and $F : \Sheaf\,J\,(\ModuleCat.\{u\}\,k)$ an abelian sheaf (with $J$ admitting weak sheafification of $\mathrm{Type}\,u$, a sheafification of $\ModuleCat.\{u\}\,k$, and a $\HasExt$ instance on $\Sheaf\,J\,(\ModuleCat.\{u\}\,k)$). For $n : \mathbb N$ and $X : C$:
  \[
    \HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,X \;:=\; \Ext^n\bigl((\mathtt{presheafToSheaf}\,J\,(\ModuleCat\,k)).\mathrm{obj}\,((\yoneda \circ \mathtt{free}_k).\mathrm{obj}\,X),\; F\bigr) \;\in\; \mathrm{Type}\,u,
  \]
  where $\mathtt{free}_k := \ModuleCat.\mathtt{free}\,k : \mathrm{Type}\,u \to \ModuleCat.\{u\}\,k$ is Mathlib's free $k$-module functor (\texttt{Mathlib/Algebra/Category/ModuleCat/Adjunctions.lean}). Carries a $\Module\,k$ instance through the same $\HasExt$ + $\Linear\,k$ chain that powers $\HModule$, accessible via the \lstinline{noncomputable abbrev} reducibility — under \lstinline{def}, instance synthesis would fail (cf. iter-009 design rationale).
\end{definition}

\begin{proof}
  \leanok
  \uses{def:Scheme_HModule, thm:HasSheafify_Opens_ModuleCatK, thm:HasExt_Sheaf_Opens_ModuleCatK}
  Direct mirror of Mathlib's \lstinline{Sheaf.H'} (file \texttt{Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/SheafCohomology/Basic.lean}). The body is the one-line term
  \[
    \mathtt{Abelian.Ext}\,((\mathtt{presheafToSheaf}\,\_\,\_).\mathrm{obj}\,((\yoneda \circ (\Functor.\whiskeringRight\,\_\,\_\,\_).\mathrm{obj}\,(\ModuleCat.\mathtt{free}\,k)).\mathrm{obj}\,X))\,F\,n.
  \]
  Plan-agent \texttt{lean\_run\_code} probe (iter-013) confirms it typechecks end-to-end against current Mathlib + project state, kernel-only axioms (\lstinline{propext}, \lstinline{Classical.choice}, \lstinline{Quot.sound}); $\Module.\mathtt{finrank}\,k\,(\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,X) : \mathbb N$ also probes successfully through the abbrev's reducibility.
\end{proof}

\begin{remark}[Why this is the iter-013 target, not the iso \texorpdfstring{$\HModulePrime\,F\,n\,\top \cong \HModule\,F\,n$}{H'(F)(top) ≅ H(F)}]
  Mathlib's \texttt{Basic.lean} (lines 30–35) explicitly leaves the iso $\HModule\,F\,n \cong (\mathtt{cohomologyPresheaf}\,F\,n).\mathrm{obj}\,(\mathrm{op}\,U)$ for $U$ terminal as a \texttt{TODO}: it is not currently proved in Mathlib for $\AddCommGrpCat$-valued sheaves. We do not attempt it here either — iter-013 only adds the API; Mathlib will catch up to the iso. Iter-014+ will define the $\cohomologyPresheaf$ functor, after which the iso (when Mathlib provides it) propagates to $\ModuleCat\,k$ flavor for free.
\end{remark}

\begin{remark}[Toward Mayer-Vietoris (iter-014+)]
  Mathlib's Mayer-Vietoris LES (\texttt{Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/SheafCohomology/MayerVietoris.lean}) for an abelian sheaf $F$ and a Mayer-Vietoris square $S$ takes the shape
  \[
    \cdots \to F.\HPrime\,n\,S.X_4 \to F.\HPrime\,n\,S.X_2 \oplus F.\HPrime\,n\,S.X_3 \to F.\HPrime\,n\,S.X_1 \to F.\HPrime\,(n+1)\,S.X_4 \to \cdots
  \]
  Substituting $\HModulePrime$ for $F.\HPrime$ on the $\ModuleCat\,k$ side gives the iter-014+ target. Iter-013 does \emph{not} state or prove the LES; it only lands the carrier.
\end{remark}

